'''Shidori Jinja''' (倭文神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]], [[:en:Fujinomiya, Shizuoka|Fujinomiya]]. It is a {{ill|Shikinaisha|de|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|zh|Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}} and its former {{ill|shrine Rank|de|Schreinrang|ja|社格|zh|神社等级|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/shrine Rank|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=shrine rank|WD=Q10444029}} was that of a {{ill|village shrine|de|Dorfschrein|ja|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|zh|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Village_shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}.

==History==
In the '''[[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]''' (Vol. 9, Shingi 9), Shidori Jinja is recorded as one of the '''[[:en:Fuji District, Shizuoka|Three shrines of Fuji District]]''' and is identified as the same shrine. Also, in the same ''Engishiki'' (Vol. 24, Shukei section), “thirty-one bolts of woven textile (倭文卅一端)” are listed among Suruga Province’s tribute items, suggesting that the local 倭文部 (Shitori-be) lived in this area. In the Middle Ages, the local Suruga power '''{{ill|Fuji clan|de|Fuji Klan|ja|富士氏|zh|富士氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fuji clan|qq=|1=Fuji clan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11456091}}''' is said to have worshipped here.<ref>
岡田米夫、『日本史小百科 神社』、近藤出版、1977年、146頁
</ref>

